<en-note><div>Installing from the Ports Tree</div><div><br/></div><div># Always update the ports treee</div><div>=&gt; sudo portsnap fetch update</div><div><br/></div><div># The Webmin ports location</div><div>=&gt; cd /usr/ports/sysutils/webmin</div><div>=&gt; sudo make install clean</div><div><br/></div><div><span style="font-style: italic; color: rgb(146, 146, 146);">After installing Webmin for the first time you should perform the following</span></div><div><span style="font-style: italic; color: rgb(146, 146, 146);">steps as root:</span></div><div><span style="font-style: italic; color: rgb(146, 146, 146);">* Configure Webmin by running /usr/local/lib/webmin/setup.sh</span></div><div><span style="font-style: italic; color: rgb(146, 146, 146);">* Add webmin_enable=&quot;YES&quot; to your /etc/rc.conf</span></div><div><span style="font-style: italic; color: rgb(146, 146, 146);">* Start Webmin for the first time by running &quot;service webmin start&quot;</span></div><div><br/></div><div><span style="font-style: italic; color: rgb(146, 146, 146);">The parameters requested by </span><a style="font-style: italic; color: rgb(146, 146, 146);" href="http://setup.sh">setup.sh</a><span style="font-style: italic; color: rgb(146, 146, 146);"> may then be changed from within Webmin</span></div><div><span style="font-style: italic; color: rgb(146, 146, 146);">itself.</span></div><div><br/></div><div><span style="color: rgb(121, 121, 121);"># Configuring the Webmin</span></div><div><span style="color: rgb(121, 121, 121);"># </span><span style="color: rgb(255, 38, 0);">Note: The Webmin uses its own webserver and it supports SSL if only if the system has</span></div><div><span style="color: rgb(255, 38, 0);"># the “Perl SSLeay library” installed.</span><span style="color: rgb(121, 121, 121);"> So, don’t look in the Apache Server configuration for ot!</span></div><div><br/></div><div>=&gt;<b> sudo</b><font color="#941100"> /usr/local/lib/webmin/</font><font color="#009051">setup.sh</font></div><div>    Log file directory [/var/log/webmin]: &lt;Entrer&gt;</div><div>    Full path to perl (default /usr/local/bin/perl): &lt;Enter&gt;</div><div>    Web server port (default 10000): 2017</div><div>    Login name (default admin):  <font color="#0433ff">khasanov</font></div><div>    Login password: <font color="#ff2600">Hydrogen***3</font></div><div>    Password again: <font color="#ff2600">H*gen*3</font></div><div>    Use SSL (y/n):<font color="#0433ff"> y</font></div><div><br/></div><div><font color="#a9a9a9"># Enable the Webmin in the &quot;<b>/etc/rc.conf</b>”</font></div><div>=&gt;<b> sudo vim</b> /etc/rc.conf &amp;&amp; add the <b>webmin_enable=“YES”</b></div><div><br/></div><div><font color="#a9a9a9"># Start the Webmin Service:</font></div><div>=&gt;<b> sudo</b><font color="#941100"> /usr/local/etc/rc.d</font>/<b>webmin</b><font color="#009051"> start</font></div><div><br/></div><div><font color="#a9a9a9"># To login the Webmin Management:</font></div><div><font color="#a9a9a9"># If the Pearl SSLeay installed : </font></div><div><a href="https://192.168.100.150:2017">https://192.168.100.150:2017</a></div><div><a href="https://vmfreebsd:2017">https://vmfreebsd:2017</a>  </div><div><br/></div><div># If not:</div><div><a href="http://192.168.100.150:2017">http://192.168.100.150:2017</a></div><div><a href="http://vmfreebsd:2017">http://vmfreebsd:2017</a></div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div> </div></en-note>
